Package com.cafean.client.ui.util

Class UndoableVersionChange

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.ui.util.UndoableVersionChange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.swing.undo.UndoableEdit
    public class UndoableVersionChange
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.swing.undo.UndoableEdit
    This is an UndoableEdit that stores a version change for a component. This allows the user to undo a change in the version of a component without building an appropriate StateEdit for the component. This assists with editing large components.

    • Constructor Detail

      • UndoableVersionChange

        public UndoableVersionChange​(AbstractComponent comp,
                             java.lang.String title)
        Creates a new instance of UndoableVersioning. Pass the component before the version number has changed, then call end when the version number has changed. The title field allows the developer to custom set the title for this undo.
